      "rationale": "Normalized index of agreement and mean absolute percentage error were computed across all five operating points. Agreement within 12% for hemolysis index satisfies Gradation 2 output comparison requirements."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QOI used in validation (hemolysis index) must directly correspond to the clinical decision metric (RH < 1) at Gradation 2.",
      "rationale": "The relative hemolysis index RH is the direct QOI and maps one-to-one to the regulatory acceptance criterion. No surrogate QOIs were introduced."
    },
    {
