      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU per scoping decision.",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is scoped out at Model Risk Level 2 for this device class. The operating team consists of trained simulation engineers with documented competency records; no formal Gradation-level assessment is required by the applicable ASME V&V 40 risk matrix at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model form uncertainty arising from turbulence closure and hemolysis power-law constitutive model must be evaluated through sensitivity analysis and literature benchmarking.",
      "rationale": "A qualitative assessment of model form uncertainty was conducted through an extensive review of published CFD hemolysis literature and turbulence model sensitivity studies. Three turbulence closures (SST k-ω, realizable k-ε, and RSM) were compared against experimental hemolysis measurements from Taskin et al. (2012) and Fraser et al. (2011). The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model was benchmarked against the modified Heuser-Opitz correlation; differences in predicted hemolysis index remained within the experimental scatter band across all operating points. Subject-matter expert review concluded that the selected model form is appropriate for the COU and that residual model form uncertainty does not alter the Accepted decision. This qualitative evaluation, supported by the breadth of literature corroboration and the conservative RH < 1 acceptance margin achieved (mean RH = 0.71), provides sufficient confidence that model form uncertainty is adequately controlled for a Class II device at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU per scoping decision.",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty quantification is not mandated at MRL 2 for this device class. Input parameters (viscosity, density, hematocrit) were set to nominal literature values with documented sources."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU per scoping decision.",
      "rationale": "Sample variability assessment is scoped out at MRL 2. A single representative pump geometry was used for both simulation and validation experiment."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2 for this COU per scoping decision.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between validation experiment and COU is addressed implicitly through the direct use of the FDA generic pump geometry and clinically representative operating conditions. Formal Gradation-level assessment is not required at MRL 2."
    }
